{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9cfe198-7ecf-4741-8e56-4c4b3e4a2b1e","content":"Yes, you will. **All three of your target frameworks are incompatible with MSTest v3.**\n\nMSTest v3 raised the minimum supported frameworks to **.NET Framework 4.7.2** and **.NET 6.0**. Your current targets fall short:\n\n| Current Target | Issue | Minimum for MSTest v3 |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net462` | Too old | `net472` |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | EOL, too old | `net6.0` |\n| `net5.0` | EOL, too old | `net6.0` |\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n\n1. **Package consolidation** — In v3, `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` are replaced by a single `MSTest` package (or the `MSTest.Sdk` project SDK).\n2. **Breaking API changes** — Some attributes and behaviors changed (e.g., `DataRow` type-checking is stricter, `Assert.ThrowsException` no longer catches derived types by default).\n\nYou'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to at least `net472;net6.0` before upgrading.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fbea343a-892b-44b9-b4e6-817a943f337b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me analyze the project. The user has:\n\n1. **Target frameworks**: `net5.0`, `net462`, `netcoreapp3.1`\n2. **MSTest packages**: `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` v2.2.10\n3. **Test SDK**: `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` v17.5.0\n\nNow, MSTest v3 has some important compatibility requirements:\n\n1. **Minimum supported frameworks**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n   - .NET Framework 4.6.2 (`net462`) — MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.7.2 or later\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` — MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0 or later (netcoreapp3.1 is out of support)\n   - `net5.0` — Also not supported by MSTest v3, which requires .NET 6.0+\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: In MSTest v3, the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single `MSTest` package (or you can use the MSTest SDK).\n\n3. **Breaking changes**: Various API changes, attribute changes, etc.\n\nSo the main compatibility issues are that all three target frameworks fall below MSTest v3's minimum requirements, and the package structure has changed significantly.","outputTokens":683,"requestId":"63C7:183DE:3CEF274:43193D4:6A02FAE1"},"id":"ae2f3a64-203a-448b-9d6c-95cc42b696fb","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:03:32.376Z","parentId":"62626869-59fd-45c5-9f9d-7895e4d1bea1"}
